overview: The user initiated a project to develop a web-based sleep
  questionnaire application, providing a Statement of Work (SOW). The core
  requirements included implementing a database for questionnaire responses,
  creating an admin dashboard for data access, and setting up authentication
  middleware. The chosen database solution was NeonDB (PostgreSQL) integrated
  with Prisma. The implementation involved updating demographic fields in the
  questionnaire to align with the SOW, defining a  model
  in Prisma, and creating API endpoints for data submission, retrieval, and CSV
  export. A key decision was to use a simple password-based authentication
  system for the admin dashboard. Initially, a custom session management
  approach was taken, but this was later refined and simplified by leveraging
  Next.js middleware for more efficient and cleaner route protection. The entire
  system, including database connectivity, API functionality, and
  authentication, was thoroughly tested and confirmed to be working as expected.
